snippet: All of the weddings right here on one handy page for you.
lead_paragraph: Dr. Regina Maree Myers and Joshua Alexander Kulick met through a dating app Sept. 24, 2016 — shortly after each had moved to Philadelphia from New York — and went on a first date to a bar later that evening. He said he knew the first date would be different when she crossed the street and walked toward him.

abstract: The couple met in 2016 through the dating app Coffee Meets Bagel.
snippet: The couple met in 2016 through the dating app Coffee Meets Bagel.
lead_paragraph: Mumu Xu and Joseph Evan Borson were married March 30 at the National Museum of Women in the Arts in Washington. Mirosia Martin, a friend of the bride who was designated as a temporary officiant by the Superior Court for the District of Columbia, officiated. Jesse Cohen, a friend of the groom, took part in the ceremony.

abstract: Aaron Boone has a team capable of ending an intolerable title drought. But to meet the lofty expectations of no less than Mariano Rivera, the Yankees must keep getting it done against the lowly.
snippet: Aaron Boone has a team capable of ending an intolerable title drought. But to meet the lofty expectations of no less than Mariano Rivera, the Yankees must keep getting it done against the lowly.
lead_paragraph: There were no proclamations from Aaron Boone at the start of this Yankees season, no guarantee in March of glory in October. That is not how baseball works, and Boone knows it in his bones. The Boone family — grandfather Ray, father Bob, and brothers Aaron and Bret — played 58 distinguished seasons in the majors and won just two World Series.

abstract: More than most, he understood the grave challenges facing the West at the end of World War I.
snippet: More than most, he understood the grave challenges facing the West at the end of World War I.
lead_paragraph: At 11 a.m. on Nov. 11, 1918, Winston Churchill was looking out of the window of his Ministry of Munitions, toward Trafalgar Square in London, waiting for the great bell of Big Ben to sound, telling Britons that World War I was finally over.

abstract: The growing prominence of the B.D.S. movement — and the backlash to it — is widening fault lines from college campuses to Capitol Hill.
snippet: The growing prominence of the B.D.S. movement — and the backlash to it — is widening fault lines from college campuses to Capitol Hill.
lead_paragraph: On June 9, 2016, the committee tasked with drafting the new Democratic Party platform held its second day of hearings at the Omni Shoreham Hotel, in the upscale Woodley Park neighborhood of Washington. The platform, which is rewritten every presidential-election year, is meant to express a consensus among Democrats on the major issues of the day. The afternoon session, on “America’s role in the world,” included discussions of platform language on the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. At stake was whether Democrats would reaffirm the party’s strongly pro-Israel position or make some concessions to the Palestinians.
